# ffmpeg-core.wasm (30.7 MiB) must stay OUT of git: Cloudflare's CDN build
# (Pages or Workers assets, either CI) hard-fails any deploy containing a file
# over 25 MiB, which froze alloflow-cdn.pages.dev from 2026-07-03 until found.
# The file stays on the local disk: Firebase hosting and the desktop bundle
# deploy from the working tree, not from a git clone, so they still ship it.
# deploy.sh Step 6 runs `git add desktop/web-app/public/` every deploy - this
# ignore entry is what stops the wasm from being silently re-added forever.
# To restore on a fresh clone (only needed for desktop packaging / Firebase):
#   npm pack @ffmpeg/core@0.12.10 && extract package/dist/umd/ffmpeg-core.wasm here
ffmpeg-core.wasm
